\layout Abstract

An ionospheric model with a minimum number of parameters, and a minimum
 number of assumptions, is investigated.
 It is the basis for a practical procedure for ionospheric calibration for
 LOFAR.
 In addition to astronomical measurements on bright sources, it also proposes
 to use a network of GPS receivers.
 The MIM approach has more applications.
 
